                    "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> A living creature steps on any part of the floor not enclosed by the summoning circle; <strong>Effect</strong> One round after a creature touches the triggering area, the door to the room slams shut and locks (two DC 20 Thievery checks to pick) and a barbazu devil (<i>Pathfinder Bestiary</i> 88) appears in the summoning circle. The devil rolls initiative and remains for 3d6 rounds, after which the spell ends and the devil disappears. The devil also disappears if someone disables the trap before the duration expires. The summoned devil can use 3 actions each round and can use reactions, unlike most summoned creatures.</p>"
